(3) No more than four hundred ninety-nine (499) students must be in an
amount that is no more than two hundred dollars ($200).
(d) An eligible school that receives a grant pursuant to subsection (c) shall
provide feminine hygiene products, at no charge, to a student if the student does not
otherwise have feminine hygiene products available for use.
(e) An LEA or public charter school may provide feminine hygiene products, at
no charge, for student use in all women's and girls' bathrooms and locker rooms in an
eligible school building where instruction is provided, excluding any bathrooms and
locker rooms specifically designated for teacher or staff use.
(f) The department of education may develop policies and provide guidance to
LEAs and public charter schools to assist LEAs and public charter schools in complying
with this section.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
